{"lemma": "دارَ", "slug": "دارَ", "root": "د.#.ر", "root_slug": "د-_-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/د-_-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "دار", "root": "دور", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 48}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 3, "pos_tags": ["adj", "noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 9}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n12341", "n13382", "n13388"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8E"}}, "translations": {"en": "to go round", "fa": "چرخیدن", "ur": "گردنا", "tr": "dönmek", "id": "berputar", "bn": "ঘোরা", "es": "dar vueltas", "fr": "tourner", "de": "sich drehen", "ru": "вращаться", "zh": "绕行"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "adj", "gloss": "flowing copiously"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "productive, rich, lucrative"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "profitable"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to turn, to revolve, to rotate", "examples": [{"text": "تَدُورُ ٱلْأَرْضُ حَوْلَ ٱلشَّمْسِ.", "english": "The Earth revolves around the Sun."}]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to go around, to circulate"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to go around, to move around"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "house"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "building, structure, edifice"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "land, country"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Derived from the active participle of the verb دَرَّ (darra, “to flow copiously”).\n\nThe noun originally referred to the buildings surrounding a court. Cognate with Akkadian 𒂦 (dūrum, “city wall”) and Biblical Hebrew דּוּר (dûr, “to move in a circle”), דָּר (dār, “to dwell”) and דּוֹר (dôr, “habitation”)."}, "ipa": ["/daː.ra/", "/daːr/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n12341", "headword_ar": "دَارٌّ", "root": "dr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dir~apN", "text_ar": "دِرَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b2-  Also, (S, Msb, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daruwrN", "text_ar": "دَرُورٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, Msb, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dar~aA='u", "text_ar": "دَرَّا=ءُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mudir~N", "text_ar": "مُدِرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) A she-camel, (S, A, K,) or ewe, or she-goat, (Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "abounding with milk; having much milk:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, Msb, K:) pl. (of the first, S, Msb)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dur~aA=rN", "text_ar": "دُرَّا=رٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, Msb, K;) and one says also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ibilN dururN", "text_ar": "اـِبِلٌ دُرُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daruwrN", "text_ar": "دَرُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the CK and in my MS. copy of the K"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Abl daruwrN", "text_ar": "ابل دَرُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ibilN dur~arN", "text_ar": "اـِبِلٌ دُرَّرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(also a pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daruwrN", "text_ar": "دَرُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the CK and in my MS. copy of the K"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Abl dararN", "text_ar": "ابل دَرَرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]): (K, accord. to the TA:) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "darwrN", "text_ar": "دَرورٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "applied to an udder signifies the same: (TA:) [and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "midoraArN", "text_ar": "مِدْرَارٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also app. signifies the same; for you say] ―         -b3-  ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "samaA='N midoraArN", "text_ar": "سَمَا=ءٌ مِدْرَارٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A sky pouring down abundance of rain:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K:) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saHaAbapN midoraArN", "text_ar": "سَحَابَةٌ مِدْرَارٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a cloud pouring down much rain."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rizoqN daAr~N", "text_ar": "رِزْقٌ دَارٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Continual, uninterrupted, sustenance,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "means of subsistence."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAr~N", "text_ar": "دَارٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dariyrN", "text_ar": "دَرِيرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "A lamp"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "giving light, shining,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "shining brightly."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Msb", "K", "A", "TA"]}, {"entry_id": "n13382", "headword_ar": "دَارَ", "root": "dwr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaduwru", "text_ar": "يَدُورُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daworN", "text_ar": "دَوْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dawaraAnN", "text_ar": "دَوَرَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, A, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "duw^uwrN", "text_ar": "دُوُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "madaArN", "text_ar": "مَدَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Lth, T;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AstdAr", "text_ar": "استدار", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (M, A, Msb, K;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AdAr", "text_ar": "ادار", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (M;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, went, moved,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "turned, round; circled; revolved; returned to the place from which he,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, began to move."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b2-  You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAruwA", "text_ar": "دَارُوا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hawolahu", "text_ar": "حَوْلَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AstdArwA", "text_ar": "استداروا", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They went round it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dAr Hawola Albayoti", "text_ar": "دار حَوْلَ البَيْتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AstdAr", "text_ar": "استدار", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He went round the house"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Kaabeh"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Msb.) Z and others dislike the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dArbiAlbayoti", "text_ar": "داربِالبَيْتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [which seems to have been used in the same sense as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dAr Hawolahu", "text_ar": "دار حَوْلَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] preferring the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TaAfa biAlbayoti", "text_ar": "طَافَ بِالبَيْتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", because of the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dAr baAld~uwaAri", "text_ar": "دار بَالدُّوَارِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He went round about in the circuit called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ald~uwaAr", "text_ar": "الدُّوَار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "round the idol called by the same name."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bihi", "text_ar": "بِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AstdAr", "text_ar": "استدار", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "mostly signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It encircled,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "surrounded,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "encompassed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "it.] ―         -b3-  [You say also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dAr bayonahumo", "text_ar": "دار بَيْنَهُمْ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a thing, as, for instance, a wine-cup)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "went round,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "circulated, among them."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "And]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dAr", "text_ar": "دار"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alfalaku fiY madaArihi", "text_ar": "الفَلَكُ فِى مَدَارِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The firmament,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "celestial orb"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sphere, revolved upon its axis"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (A:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dawaraAnu", "text_ar": "دَوَرَانُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alfalaki", "text_ar": "الفَلَكِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the consecutive incessant motions of the several parts of the firmament."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) ―         -b4-  Hence the saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daArati AlmasoA^alapu", "text_ar": "دَارَتِ المَسْاَلَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daworN", "text_ar": "دَوْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The question formed a circle; one of its propositions depending for proof upon another following it, and perhaps this upon another, and so on, and the latter or last depending upon the admission of the first."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) [And in like manner,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dAr", "text_ar": "دار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daworN", "text_ar": "دَوْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He reasoned in a circle."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b5-  It is said in a trad., ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a Alz~amaAna qadi A@sotadaAra", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ الزَّمَانَ قَدِ ا@سْتَدَارَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kahayoy^atihi yawoma xaloqi A@ll~`hi Als~am`waAti wa AlA^aroDa", "text_ar": "كَهَيْيَتِهِ يَوْمَ خَلْقِ ا@للّٰهِ السَّمٰوَاتِ وَ الاَرْضَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily time hath come round to the like of the state in which it was on the day of God's creating the heavens and the earth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "this was said by Mohammad after he had forbidden the practice of intercalating a lunar month, by which the Arabs had long imperfectly adjusted their lunar year to the solar.] (TA.) And one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daArati AlA^ay~aAmu", "text_ar": "دَارَتِ الاَيَّامُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The days came round in their turns"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S and Msb and K in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dwl", "text_ar": "دول"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yawomN laA yaduwru fiY $ahorihi", "text_ar": "يَوْمٌ لَا يَدُورُ فِى شَهْرِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A day"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the week"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that does not come round again in its month:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as the last Wednesday, &c.]. (Mujáhid, TA voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dubaArN", "text_ar": "دُبَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.].) [And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dAr", "text_ar": "دار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is said of an event, as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It came about."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "See an ex. in a verse cited in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A*", "text_ar": "اذ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dArbihi", "text_ar": "داربِهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It went round with him; as the ground and the sea do"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "apparently"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with a person sick by reason of vertigo,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "giddiness in the head."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "myd", "text_ar": "ميد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". [See also 4.]) ―         -b7-  One says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bimaA fiY", "text_ar": "بِمَا فِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AstdAr", "text_ar": "استدار", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qalobiY", "text_ar": "قَلْبِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He comprehended"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as though he encircled]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what was in my heart."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A.) ―         -b8-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN yaduwru", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ يَدُورُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY A^arobaEi nisowapK", "text_ar": "عَلَى اَرْبَعِ نِسْوَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one has within the circuit of his rule and care four wives,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "women."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN yaduwru Hawola fulaAnapa wayujam~i$uhaA", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ يَدُورُ حَوْلَ فُلَانَةَ وَيُجَمِّشُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a man has within his power and care such a female, and toys, dallies, wantons,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "holds amorous converse, with her"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A and TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HwD", "text_ar": "حوض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anaA A^aduwru Hawola *`lika AlA^amori", "text_ar": "اَنَا اَدُورُ حَوْلَ ذٰلِكَ الاَمْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I have within my compass,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "power, and care, that thing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "affair"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S and A in art"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HwD", "text_ar": "حوض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)       -A2-  See also 4, in four places."}], "source_refs": ["S", "M", "A", "Msb", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n13388", "headword_ar": "دَارٌ", "root": "dwr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", [originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dawarN", "text_ar": "دَوَرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as will be seen below,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A house; a mansion;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and especially"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a house of a large size, comprising a court;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a house comprising several sets of apartments and a court;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayotN", "text_ar": "بَيْتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";)]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a place of abode which comprises a building,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "buildings, and a court,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "space in which is no building:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M, K:) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daArapN", "text_ar": "دَارَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M, K:) or the latter is a more special term; (S;) meaning any"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "particular house;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the former being a generic term: (MF:) accord. to IJ, it is from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAra", "text_ar": "دَارَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaduwru", "text_ar": "يَدُورُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; because of the many movements of the people in it: (M:) it is of the fem. gender: (S, Msb:) and sometimes masc.; (S, K;) as in the Kur xvi. 32, as meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mavowaY", "text_ar": "مَثْوَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mawoDiE", "text_ar": "مَوْضِع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) or as being a gen. n.: (MF:) pl. (of pauc., S)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^adow^urN", "text_ar": "اَدْوُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^adowurN", "text_ar": "اَدْوُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=durN", "text_ar": "ا=دُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Abu-l- Hasan, AAF, Msb, K,) formed by transposition, (Msb,) [for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^awodurN", "text_ar": "اَوْدُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^adowaArN", "text_ar": "اَدْوَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^adoyaArN", "text_ar": "اَدْيَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^adowirapN", "text_ar": "اَدْوِرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, K,) and (of mult., S)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "diyaArN", "text_ar": "دِيَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, K,) like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jibaAlN", "text_ar": "جِبَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "